hopobject.body: Could I have an application form? altamont pharmacy hours Half a million tourists pour into Brazil to celebrate alongside more than one million Brazilians. In 2011, the crowds in the centre of the city exceeded two million revellers. The Rio Carnival began in the 1840s, as a rather more sedate masked ball, where people would dance polkas and waltzes. By 1917, the newly invented local dance called “samba” had become an integral part of the pre-Lent celebration. No one knows where the word originated but one theory suggests it is a corruption of semba in the West African Kikongo language, which translates as “a blow struck with the belly button”.
